**Reviewed:** the Olivia Wilde Type 3 draft (full read + a light reality check on her biography).

**The two biggest issues I flagged:**

1. **The first marriage is missing entirely** — at 19, in the same window she renamed herself "Wilde," she eloped with Tao Ruspoli (an Italian prince/filmmaker) and stayed married 2003–2011. That's the single most dramatic self-authoring act in her life, and the "keeps becoming someone new" section skips it. Adding it would actually *strengthen* the thesis, not just patch a hole.

2. **"The spitting clip" and "the salad dressing" are name-dropped but never explained** — they read as 2022-Twitter in-jokes a fresh reader won't follow. Give each a half-clause of context or cut them.

I also noted that motherhood is nearly invisible despite the custody petition being the emotional core (the reader never learns there are two kids), the CinemaCon envelope gets retold four times, and that the journalist-dynasty frame + the self-renaming insight are the standout strengths to preserve. No body edits made, per the command.

